  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2017-12-21",
    "date": "2019-08-16T19:04:13Z",
    "text": "Mitigating the Methamphetamine Epidemic and Promoting Tribal Health Act or the Mitigating METH Act\n\nThis bill amends the 21st Century Cures Act to make Indian tribes eligible for funding under the opioid grant program for states. In addition, the bill expands the grant program to allow states and tribes to use grants for the prevention and treatment of the use of other substances, such as methamphetamine, that have a substantial public health impact on states or tribes."
  },
